      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINIMISE (7) came off three trials and picked up nicely beaten 3L over 1400m this track on debut. There was a lot to like about that and the step up to 1600m looks ideal. Maps well and Milnes sticks aboard. VALOR BOUND (3) resumed in the same race but was slow into stride, expected to need the outing regardless. He'd switched from a leading Victorian barn and three-back on debut was only beaten 2L over this trip at Donald.  Needs a good ride from the outside gate but a much better effort is likely. MIZZEN JIB (2) debuted against the above pair and it was a fair effort after settling well back. Gets Crowther today and can get closer with the extra fitness. FINE ACE (5) peaks and has been mixing the form in sprints. He didn't manage a wide gate at The Parks last time but showed enough three back at Oakbank to suggest she will win races. Has a 2kg claim and there's promise that the step-up to 1600m will suit.",
